{"descriptions":[{"id":1349,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn Literary Tibetan, the adversative connective \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྟེ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;but\u0026rdquo; has several variants according to the last letter of the preceding syllable.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྟེ་\u003c/span\u003e is used after \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eག་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eང་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབ་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའ་\u003c/span\u003e and vowels \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདེ་\u003c/span\u003e is used after \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཏེ་\u003c/span\u003e is used after \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eན་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eར་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eལ་\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eས་\u003c/span\u003e and the \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eད་དྲག་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn speech, the three are all pronounced \u003cem\u003ede\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThis particle has a range of functions in Literary Tibetan. In the spoken language, by contrast, it is used only to introduce an opposition between two phrases or a concession, and may be translated by \u0026ldquo;but\u0026rdquo; or \u0026ldquo;although.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe particle \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྟེ་\u003c/span\u003e is only used after certain auxiliaries. It usually appears in the following combinations: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་དེ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡོད་རེད་དེ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདུག་སྟེ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་ཏེ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརེད་ཏེ་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདྲ་པོ་རེད་དེ་གཅིག་པ་རང་མ་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Even though they\u0026rsquo;re similar, they\u0026rsquo;re not quite identical.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁོང་ལ་དངུལ་ཡོད་རེད་དེ།\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབེད་སྤྱོད་བཏང་གི་ཡོད་མ་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;He has money but he doesn\u0026rsquo;t use it.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྐད་ཡག་པོ་འདུག་སྟེ་གཞས་བཏང་གི་མི་འདུག\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Although she has a nice voice, she doesn\u0026rsquo;t sing.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:42 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:42 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}